BusinessName.BusinessNameLine2Txt: THE NEW YORK CITY WATERSHEDS INC

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ADDRESS SURFACE-WATER QUALITY THROUGH LAND CONSERVATION WHILE SUPPORTING THE ECONOMIC VIABILITY OF AGRICULTURE AND FORESTRY IN THE NEW YORK CITY WATERSHED REGION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO SUPPORT THE ECONOMIC VIABILITY OF AGRICULTURE AND FORESTRY THROUGH THE PROTECTION OF WATER QUALITY AND THE PROMOTION OF LAND CONSERVATION IN THE NEW YOTK CITY WATERSHED REGION.
IRS990.Desc: WATERSHED AGRICULTURAL PROGRAM (WAP) - WORKS WITH INDIVIDUAL FARMERS ON A VOLUNTARY BASIS TO CREATE AND IMPLEMENT WHOLE FARM PLANS DESIGNED TO MITIGATE NONPOINT-SOURCE WATER POLLUTION FROM FARMING ACTIVITIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: CONSERVATION EASEMENT PROGRAM (CEP) - WORKS TO CONSERVE FARM AND FOREST LAND BY PURCHASING THE DEVELOPMENT RIGHTS TO THESE LANDS. PERMANENT PROTECTION OF THIS "UNDERDEVELOPED" LAND THROUGH CONSERVATION EASEMENTS IS ULTIMATELY THE MOST LASTING WATER QUALITY PROTECTION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: WATERSHED FORESTRY PROGRAM (WFP) - WORKS WITH FOREST LANDOWNERS, FORESTORS, AND LOGGERS ON A VOLUNTARY BASIS TO DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT FOREST MANAGEMENT PLANS. THE PLANS GIVE LANDOWNERS AN OPPORUNITY TO LEARN ABOUT THE IMPORTANT RESOURCE THEY OWN AND ITS MANY VALUES SUCH AS LUMBER, FIREWOOD, AESTHETICS, HABITAT, OPEN SPACE RECREATION, ETC

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: ECONOMIC VIABILITY AND STEWARTSHIP PROGRAMS OUTREACH - WORKS TO RAISE AWARENESS AMONG THE GENERAL PUBLIC, DEVELOP CONNECTIONS BETWEEN WATERSHED PRODUCERS/PRODUCTS & NEW YORK CITY CONSUMERS AS WELL AS SUPPORT FARM & FORESTRY LANDOWNERS IN THE NEW YORK CITY REGION THROUGH A NUMBER OF PROGRAMS INCLUDING EDUCATIONAL WORKSHOPS, SEMINARS, GRASSROOT FESTIVALS/EVENTS, FARM/FOREST TOURS AND ECONOMIC SUSTAINABILITY INITIATIVES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE D, PAGE 1, PART II, LINE 5
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WATERSHED AGRICULTURAL COUNCIL (WAC) HAS AN EASEMENT APPROVAL POLICY WHERE A LANDOWNER SIGNS A PURCHASE AND SALES CONTRACT TO SELL A CONSERVATION EASEMENT TO THE WAC, AND AN EASEMENT COMMITTEE REPRESENTATIVE WILL PRESENT THE COUNCIL WITH THE INFORMATION FOR THEIR CONSIDERATION AND APPROVAL. THE EASEMENT COMMITTEE SHALL DEVELOP GUIDELINES FOR THE ACQUISITION OF EASEMENTS WHICH SHALL INCLUDE: APPLICANT SELECTION, LAND PLANNING, APPRAISALS, OFFERS, AND PURCHASE AND SALES CONTRACTS. CONSERVATION EASEMENTS ACQUIRED BY WAC WITH NYC FUNDS SHALL REFLECT THE TERMS OF ACQUISITION AS DEFINED IN THE 1997 NYC WATERSHED MEMORANDUM OF AGREEMENT, THE CONTRACT AND SCOPE OF WORK WITH THE NYC DEP, AND EASEMENT COMMITTE GUIDELINES PERTAINING TO LAND AQUISITION. ACQUISITION OF CONSERVATION EASEMENTS SHALL BE CONDUCTED IN A MANNER THAT COMPLIES WITH ALL APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL LAWS. CONSERVATION EASEMENTS SHALL NOT BE ACQUIRED IN A MANNER WHICH WOULD JEOPARDIZE WAC'S STANDING AS A NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION. THE EASEMENT COMMITTEE SHALL DEVELOP GUIDELINES FOR THE STEWARDSHIP OF EASEMENTS WHICH SHALL INCLUDE: EASEMENT MONITORING, THE ACTIVATION OF RESERVED RIGHTS, AMENDMENTS, VIOLATIONS, NOTIFICATIONS, AND FOREST MANAGEMENT PLANS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE D, PAGE 1, PART II, LINE 9
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EASEMENTS ARE REPORTED AS A FUNCTIONAL EXPENSE ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS USING THE ACCRUAL METHOD OF ACCOUNTING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL RESOURCES TO WATERSHED AGRICULTURAL COUNCIL OF THE NEW YORK CITY WATERSHED, INC.

ECONOMIC VIABILITY AND STEWARTSHIP PROGRAMS OUTREACH - WORKS TO RAISE AWARENESS AMONG THE GENERAL PUBLIC, DEVELOP CONNECTIONS BETWEEN WATERSHED PRODUCERS/PRODUCTS & NEW YORK CITY CONSUMERS AS WELL AS SUPPORT FARM & FORESTRY LANDOWNERS IN THE NEW YORK CITY REGION THROUGH A NUMBER OF PROGRAMS INCLUDING EDUCATIONAL WORKSHOPS, SEMINARS, GRASSROOT FESTIVALS/EVENTS, FARM/FOREST TOURS AND ECONOMIC SUSTAINABILITY INITIATIVES.
THE 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE AUDIT/FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THEN BY THE FULL BOARD AT A COUNCIL MEETING.

ANNUALLY THE POLICY IS REVIEWED AT A COUNCIL MEETING AT WHICH TIME THE BOARD MEMBERS ARE ASKED TO COMPLETE THE FORMS. IT IS THEN LEFT UP TO THE COMMITTEE CHAIRS TO GET THE FORMS COMPLETED BY NON-DIRECTOR COMMITTEE MEMBERS. ANNUALLY THEY ARE SENT OUT TO STAFF FOR COMPLETION AND GIVEN TO NEW STAFF AT THE TIME OF HIRE. ALL FORMS ARE THEN REVIEWED AND SIGNED OFF ON BY THE CHAIR OF THE AUDIT AND REGULATORY COMMITTEE AND THE DIRECTOR OF OPERATIONS.
THE AMOUNT OF COMPENSATION IS PREDETERMINED IN CONTRACTS WITH NYC DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION.
MOST DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE ON THE COUNCIL'S WEBSITE; ADDITIONAL INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
